<subSubSection id="C3266529FFB3FFA6FF0CFB7DDC51FADF" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB3FFA6FF0CFB7DDC51FADF" blockId="13.[151,1436,1163,1765]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FF0CFB7DD903FB68" bold="true" box="[199,322,1235,1261]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CC49B47FFB3FFA6FE57FB7DDA65FB6B" box="[412,548,1235,1262]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.7">1.7–2.3 mm</quantity>
, 2.2–2.6 × as long as wide.Antennal club twice as long as wide, sutures obscure, basal segment subcorneous, elongated; 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FD84FB59DAC8FA94" bold="true" box="[591,649,1271,1297]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">male</emphasis>
declivity impressed, demarcated laterally by 5–6 curled tubercles, 2 or 3 of these much larger than others; interstrial setae short, as long as wide, spatulate to truncated, densely placed and broadly confused; 
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FEA3FA91D9F6FADC" bold="true" box="[360,439,1343,1369]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">female</emphasis>
declivity rounded, interstrial setae in uniseriate rows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266529FFB3FFA6FF0CFACDDA08F9D3" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB3FFA6FF0CFACDDCB9FA6F" blockId="13.[151,1436,1163,1765]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FF0CFACDD9B1FAF8" bold="true" box="[199,496,1379,1405]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F32B7632FFB3FFA6FE3DFACDDA3EFAF8" box="[502,639,1379,1405]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Previously known only from Andasibe (Perinet) where it was dissected from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FF1FFA26D93FFA24" box="[212,382,1416,1442]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cymosa">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FF1FFA26D93FFA24" box="[212,382,1416,1442]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Ocotea cymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
branches sitting on a felled tree (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B53FFB3FFA6FD20FA29DB3AFA24" author="Schedl, K. E." box="[747,891,1415,1441]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref10622" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1977) Die Scolytidae und Platypodidae Madagaskars und einiger naheliegender Inselgruppen. Mitteilungen der Forstlichen Bundes-Versuchsanstalt Wien, 119, 1 - 326." type="journal article" year="1977">Schedl 1977</bibRefCitation>
). Two females joined 
<specimenCount id="9D3AFD2BFFB3FFA6FBA6FA26DC94FA24" box="[1133,1237,1415,1442]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
, with each female tunnelling in opposite directions along the grain of the phloem and inner bark. The several new records from Ranomafana were all made together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FDFBFA7EDAD1FA6C" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[560,656,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FDFBFA7EDAD1FA6C" box="[560,656,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">P. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FD5CFA61DAB0FA6C" bold="true" box="[663,753,1487,1513]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFB3FFA6FD5CFA61DAB0FA6C" box="[663,753,1487,1513]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, in small branches of various 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FB8AFA7EDCF5FA6F" box="[1089,1204,1488,1514]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lauraceae</taxonomicName>
trees.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB3FFA6FF0CFA5DDA08F9D3" blockId="13.[151,1436,1163,1765]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
