<subSubSection id="C3266529FFB3FFA6FF0CF9F1D988F960" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFB3FFA6FF0CF9F1D988F960" blockId="13.[151,1436,1163,1765]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FF0CF9F1D97AF9FC" bold="true" box="[199,315,1631,1657]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">Remarks.</emphasis>
As indicated by the molecular data this species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FBFBF9CEDCCEF9FC" authority="Jordal, 2022" authorityName="Jordal" authorityYear="2022" box="[1072,1167,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FBFBF9CEDCCEF9FC" box="[1072,1167,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">P. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FB5DF9F1DCAEF9FC" bold="true" box="[1174,1263,1631,1657]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27B57CBFFB3FFA6FB5DF9F1DCAEF9FC" box="[1174,1263,1631,1657]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The females of the two species are very similar except 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FD86F92ADAF0F918" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[589,689,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FD86F92ADAF0F918" box="[589,689,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">P. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much larger. Based on male characters, however, particularly on the declivity, and the stout shape of the females, it is expected that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FC4EF906DC5BF944" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[901,1050,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomicoides">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FC4EF906DC5BF944" box="[901,1050,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">P. tomicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D21FFB3FFA6FB9AF906DD32F947" authority="(Schedl, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Schedl" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1105,1395,1703,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudomicracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennata">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFB3FFA6FB9AF906DC86F944" box="[1105,1223,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="338">P. pennata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B53FFB3FFA6FB1DF909DD2AF947" author="Schedl, K. E." box="[1238,1387,1703,1730]" pageId="13" pageNumber="338" pagination="51 - 85" refId="ref10566" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1965) Fauna Madagascariensis, VI. 232 Beitrag. Reichenbachia, Dresden, 5, 51 - 85." type="journal article" year="1965">Schedl, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are also members of this clade.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
